iträge zu den gesellschaftlichen und ethischen Aspekten der Nicht-Diskriminierung bei Demenz und zeigt aktuelle Desiderate und Zukunftsperspektiven auf.  aThis volume uses human rights as a benchmark for assessing the quality of clinical and nursing care for people with dementia.  afunded by Emerging Fields Initiative (EFI), Universitätsbund Erlangen-Nürnberg e. V., Friedrich-Alexander-Universität Erlangen-Nürnberg (FAU).  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn German.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 02. Mrz 2022) 0aDementiaxPatientsxCare. 0aHuman rights. 4aAlter. 4aEthik. 4aMedizin. 4aMedizinethik. 4aMedizinsoziologie. 4aMensch. 4aMenschenrechte. 4aPflege. 4aPflegeforschung. 4aRecht. 4aSoziologie. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Disease & Health Issues.2bisacsh  aAging Studies.  aCare.  aEthics.  aHuman Rights.  aHuman.  aLaw.  aMedical Ethics.  aMedicine.  aNursing Research.  aSociology of Medicine.  aSociology.1 aBielefeldt, Heiner, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBielefeldt, Heiner, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aEngedal, Knut, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrewer, Andreas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFrewer, Andreas, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aGüther, Helen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHofstetter, Hanna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHolzhauser, Luise, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHäupler, Sandra, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJablonowski, Johannes, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJoa, Wolfgang, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKlotz, Sa